# Central pinned refs for building crewborg + reading its replays.
#
# One source of truth so the build script and the replay reader agree on versions.
# Sourced by `tools/build/build_player.sh` (PLAYERS_SDK_REF) and
# `tools/build_expand_replay.sh` (CREWRIFT_REF). Bump a value here; nothing else.
#
# HOW TO EDIT: change a ref below. `main` for the SDK is auto-resolved to a commit at
# build time (so the Docker cache busts when main moves); set a SHA to pin. CREWRIFT_REF
# must be a real commit (it can't be auto-resolved — see its note).

# ── The shared player SDK crewborg (Python) builds against ────────────────────────
# Installed from the coworld-tools monorepo's `players/` subdirectory (the players repo
# moved there). The Dockerfile pip-installs
# `…coworld-tools/archive/<ref>.tar.gz#subdirectory=players`. build_player.sh resolves
# `main` to coworld-tools' current main commit via `git ls-remote`, so the pip layer's
# cache busts exactly when main moves (a literal `main` build-arg is a cache trap: the
# URL string is unchanged, so a moved main silently keeps the stale SDK). Set a SHA to pin.
#
# NB: local `uv run` ALSO installs the SDK from coworld-tools — the root pyproject.toml
# `[tool.uv.sources]` pins `players[bedrock]` to the same archive TARBALL (a tarball
# excludes submodules, sidestepping the broken `players/users/relh/co-gas` submodule that
# breaks uv's recursive git clone, coworld-tools issue #13). Keep that SHA in sync with
# this ref when you pin (uv can't auto-track `main` for a tarball — set the SHA + `uv lock`).
PLAYERS_SDK_REF=main

# ── The deployed crewrift game commit, for the replay reader ──────────────────────
# crewborg is Python and does NOT compile against crewrift, so its *build* ignores this.
# It exists for `tools/build_expand_replay.sh`, which builds the `expand_replay` binary
# that re-steps recorded replays and HASH-CHECKS every tick — so it must match the EXACT
# game commit the arena ran when it recorded the replays, or it aborts mid-replay (sparse
# output; see the event-warehouse README "version coupling").
#
# DELIBERATELY PINNED — do NOT point at `master` (it runs ahead of what's deployed and
# hash-fails). The platform exposes no commit for the deployed image, so resolve it:
#   `coworld episodes --round <id> --json` → each episode's `coworld_version`
#   (e.g. `crewrift:0.1.54` or `crewrift_prime:0.3.9`), then map to its commit and verify
#   `expand_replay` exits 0 with `trace_complete:true` on a real replay from that round.
# Known mappings (re-verify before trusting): crewrift:0.1.54 ⇒ 42fed21 (2026-06-24);
# Crewrift Prime crewrift_prime:0.3.9 ⇒ 20e3be4. Set the one matching the replays you're reading.
# How you'll know to bump: build_expand_replay starts hash-failing on FRESH replays.
CREWRIFT_REF=42fed21
